library(dplyr)

olsl$EDUC[mylfsdata$EDUC==0] <- 1


olsl <- mylfsdata %>% 
  mutate(No_Postsecondary = ifelse(EDUC == 2, 1, 0),
         Postsecondary_Certificate = ifelse(EDUC == 4, 1, 0),
         Bachelors_Degree = ifelse(EDUC == 5, 1, 0),
         Above_Bachelors_Degree = ifelse(EDUC > 6, 1, 0)
         )
hist(mylfsdata$HRLYEARN)

# log for normal distribution
hist(log(mylfsdata$HRLYEARN))

reg <- lm(log(HRLYEARN) ~ No_Postsecondary + Postsecondary_Certificate + Bachelors_Degree + Above_Bachelors_Degree,
          data = olsl)

reg_tidy <- tidy(reg, conf.int = TRUE)

summary(reg_tidy)

dow_estimate <- reg_tidy %>% 
  filter(term %in% c("No_Postsecondary", "Postsecondary_Certificate", "Bachelors_Degree", "Above_Bachelors_Degree"))
dow_estimate %>% 
  ggplot(mapping=aes(x=term,y=estimate,ymin=conf.low,ymax=conf.high))+
  geom_pointrange()+
  coord_flip()+
  labs(x="EDUC",
       y="OLS Estmiate for lm(HRLYEARN)")+
  geom_hline(yintercept=0,linetype="dashed", color="red")
